    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I have the feeling that this is what the categorical dtype is meant for? \r\nSo if you want to ensure that a certain column is always encoded consistently, regardless of the actual occurring values, you can set the categories of that column to a fixed set:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncat_type = pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(categories=['a', 'b', 'c', 'd'])\r\ndf['col'] = df['col'].astype(cat_type)\r\n```\r\n\r\nand then doing `get_dummies` should give what you want.\r\n\r\nThe above is a bit verbose, but I think we should rather think about making this easier, than further expanding `get_dummies`."
  },
